3. Gives 9000mah output or slight more as per my test (72% charge ratio). I am using honor 6X having 3340 MAH battery and following is the test result with single charge-
*From 1% to 100% - 2 Times
*From 30% to 100% - 1 Time. 
Cons :
1. Not having any fast charging capabilities.
2. Not having torch
3. There is no option to charge low input devices like smart band compared to MI powerbanks.

text:
Ok so I got mine yesterday. Not complaining about the power bank but am quite upset with the Flipkart delivery, as it took almost 7 days to get delivered. Anyway it has stylish design and good built quality. Since I haven't used it much yet so think am gonna updatey my review later. But overall it's total value for money and yes it's a made in India product so must go for it.

Edit : Well guys I'm using it still and it is working like a charm. Haven't seen any issues so far yet. Also it charges up my 3000mah cell for like 3 times easily and still left some juice in it. I've seen some guys giving bad reviews about it but it doesn't bother me. Yes it's bulky and takes time to get fully charged cuz it has huge power battery so of course it's gonna be a lil heavy. Also good things never comes in a small package lol ;) So yep a big thumbs up for this device, would surely recommend it.
